Package: surveyzones
Title: Workload-Balanced Zone Construction for Survey Field Operations
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Eduardo", "Leoni", , "eduardo.leoni@ibge.gov.br", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Constructs compact, workload-balanced geographic zones for
    survey field teams. Given a set of census tracts with access points
    and expected service times, the package computes sparse pairwise
    distances (using pluggable distance engines), solves a capacitated
    p-median problem via mixed-integer linear programming to assign tracts
    to zones, and sequences visits within each zone. Supports partitioning
    by jurisdiction and parameter sweeps for scenario comparison.
